This paper deals with problems related to low-level vision, such as depth prediction, camera motion estimation, optical flow, and segmentation of a video into static and moving regions. These are all topics that fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel framework for coordinated training of multiple neural networks, which is a topic that falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of camera motion, which is related to robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with video segmentation, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, and cs.MM, in that order.
